refine_scale_reset.title: Reset input per-particle scale
refine_scale_reset.desc: Reset input per-particle scale factors to 1.0 at the start of the job.

crg_min_res_A.title: Minimum Fit Res (A)
crg_min_res_A.desc: The minimum resolution to use during refinement of image aberrations.

crg_plot_binfactor.title: Binning to apply to plots
crg_plot_binfactor.desc: Binning makes it easier to see tilt/trefoil/tetrafoil etc in the data plots, but does not change the results

refine_res_align_max.title: Maximum align resolution (A)
refine_res_align_max.desc: Manual override for maximum resolution that is used for alignment. This value is normally set by the GS-FSC

refine_symmetry_do_align.title: Do symmetry alignment
refine_symmetry_do_align.desc: Align the input structure to the symmetry axes

refine_dynamic_mask_near_ang.title: Dynamic mask near (A)
refine_dynamic_mask_near_ang.desc: Controls extent to which mask is expanded. At the near distance, the mask value is 1.0 (in A)

refine_num_final_iterations.title: Number of extra final passes
refine_num_final_iterations.desc: Number of extra passes through the data to do after the GS-FSC resolution has stopped improving

refine_batchsize_epsilon.title: Batchsize epsilon
refine_batchsize_epsilon.desc: Controls batch size when autotuning batchsizes. Set closer to zero for larger batches

random_seed.title: Random seed
random_seed.desc: Set to null to auto generate.

refine_scale_min.title: Minimize over per-particle scale
refine_scale_min.desc: Minimize over per-particle scale at each iteration of refinement. The optimal scale will be used for backprojection as well, and will be written out at each iteration

refine_noise_init_sigmascale.title: Noise initial sigma-scale
refine_noise_init_sigmascale.desc: Scale factor initially applied to the base noise estimate

refine_ctf_global_refine.title: Optimize per-group CTF params
refine_ctf_global_refine.desc: Optimize the per-exposure-group CTF parameters (for higher-order aberrations) at each iteration of refinement. The optimal CTF will be used for backprojection as well, and will be written out at each iteration. CTF refinement will start only once refinement with current CTF values converges. Beware that with small/disordered proteins, CTF refinement may actually make resolutions worse.

refine_compute_batch_size.title: GPU batch size of images
refine_compute_batch_size.desc: Batch size of images to process at a time on the GPU. If you run out of GPU memory, try setting this to a small number to override the auto-detect procedure.

refine_clip.title: Enforce non-negativity
refine_clip.desc: Clip negative density. Probably should be false

refine_do_init_scale_est.title: Re-estimate greyscale level of input reference

refine_scale_start_iter.title: Scale min/use start iter
refine_scale_start_iter.desc: Iteration to start minimizing over per-particle scale

refine_noise_initw.title: Noise initw
refine_noise_initw.desc: Weight of the initial noise estimate (units of # of images)

refine_dynamic_mask_use_abs.title: Dynamic mask use absolute value
refine_dynamic_mask_use_abs.desc: Include negative regions if they are more negative than the threshold

refine_batch_random.title: Use random ordering of particles
refine_batch_random.desc: Whether to refine particles in random order. If False, particles are read and processed in order of input.

refine_mask.title: Mask (dynamic, static, null)
refine_mask.desc: Type of masking to use. Either "dynamic", "static", or "null"

refine_dynamic_mask_start_res.title: Dynamic mask start resolution (A)
refine_dynamic_mask_start_res.desc: Map resolution at which to start dynamic masking (in A)

crg_num_plots.title: Num. groups to plot
crg_num_plots.desc: Number of exposure groups to make plots for. After this many, stop plotting to save time.

refine_dynamic_mask_far_ang.title: Dynamic mask far  (A)
refine_dynamic_mask_far_ang.desc: Controls extent to which mask is expanded. At the far distance the mask value becomes 0.0 (in A)

refine_window.title: Window structure in real space
refine_window.desc: Softly window the structure in real space with a spherical window. Should be true

refine_batchsize_snrfactor.title: Batchsize snrfactor
refine_batchsize_snrfactor.desc: Specifies the desired improvement in SNR from the images when autotuning batchsizes. Directly multiplies the number of images in the batch

refine_symmetry.title: Symmetry
refine_symmetry.desc: Symmetry String (C, D, I, O, T). E.g. C1, D7, C4, etc

crg_do_anisomag.title: Fit Anisotropic Mag.
crg_do_anisomag.desc: Whether to fit beam anisotropic magnification.

refine_dynamic_mask_thresh_factor.title: Dynamic mask threshold (0-1)
refine_dynamic_mask_thresh_factor.desc: Level set threshold for selecting regions that are included in the dynamic mask. Probably don't need to change this

refine_gs_resplit.title: Force re-do GS split
refine_gs_resplit.desc: Force re-splitting the particles into two random gold-standard halves. If this is not set, split is preserved from input alignments (if connected)

refine_N_cmp.title: Refinement box size (voxels)
refine_N_cmp.desc: The volume size to use for refinement. Default: raw particle size

crl_min_res_A.title: Minimum Fit Res (A)
crl_min_res_A.desc: The minimum resolution to use during refinement of image aberrations.

refine_batchsize_init.title: Initial batchsize
refine_batchsize_init.desc: Number of images used in the initial iteration. Set to zero to autotune

refine_res_gsfsc_split.title: GSFSC split resolution (A)
refine_res_gsfsc_split.desc: Resolution beyond which two GS-FSC halves are independent

crl_df_range.title: Defocus Search Range (A +/-)
crl_df_range.desc: Defocus search range in Angstroms, searching both above and below the input defocus by this amount

refine_defocus_refine.title: Optimize per-particle defocus
refine_defocus_refine.desc: Minimize over per-particle defocus at each iteration of refinement. The optimal defocus will be used for backprojection as well, and will be written out at each iteration. Defocus refinement will start only once refinement with current defocus values converges. Beware that with small/disordered proteins, defocus refinement may actually make resolutions worse.

refine_N_p_zp.title: Particle ZT size E-step (pixels)
refine_N_p_zp.desc: Particle zeropad/truncation during alignment. Default: raw particle size

refine_N_p_bp.title: Particle ZT size M-step (pixels)
refine_N_p_bp.desc: Particle zeropad/truncation during backprojection. Default: raw particle size

intermediate_plots.title: Show plots from intermediate steps
intermediate_plots.desc: Hide plots from intermediate steps to speed up processing.

compute_use_ssd.title: Cache particle images on SSD
compute_use_ssd.desc: Use the SSD to cache particles. Speeds up processing significantly.

refine_noise_model.title: Noise model (white, symmetric or coloured)
refine_noise_model.desc: Noise model to be used. Valid options are white, coloured or symmetric. Symmetric is the default, meaning coloured with radial symmetry

crl_num_plots.title: Num. particles to plot
crl_num_plots.desc: Number of particles to make plots for. After this many, stop plotting to save time.

refine_ignore_dc.title: Ignore DC component
refine_ignore_dc.desc: Ignore the DC component of images. Should be true

refine_N_v.title: Volume stored size (voxels)
refine_N_v.desc: The size to store the volume during refinement. Default: raw particle size

refine_noise_priorw.title: Noise priorw
refine_noise_priorw.desc: Weight of the prior for estimating noise (units of # of images)

output_result_groups.description: All particles that were processed, including alignments
output_result_groups.title: All particles
output_result_groups.name: particles

input_slot_groups.name: particles
input_slot_groups.title: Particle stacks
input_slot_groups.description: Particle stacks to use. Multiple stacks will be concatenated.

output_results.name: alignments3D
output_results.title: Refined alignments
output_results.description: 3D alignments including pose, shift, stats, classification scores, etc.
